column1: I got my first real six-string, bought it at the five-and-dime
Played it till my fingers bled, was the summer of 69
Me and some guys from school, had a band and we tried real hard

And if I had the choice, yeah, I just wanna be there
Those were the best days of my life

I spent my evenings down at the job-in, and that's when I met you, yeah
